  "bookTitle": "Elven Priestess",
  "bookId": 61,
  "firstAcquaintance": "One of the Five Great Disasters, the Forest Disaster. The true voice of the elven race, she prevents all contact between elves and the outside world.",
  "personality": "Arrogant and short-tempered, often throwing childish tantrums and frequently clashing with others.",
  "like": "Elves, all kinds of sweets, dogs",
  "familiarData": "Her petite appearance makes people mistake her for a little girl, but she is undeniably ancient. Her body is interwoven with plants because she consumed the fruit of the Sacred Tree, transforming parts of her body into flora. This granted her a powerful and immortal body, but the cost was merging her spirit with the Sacred Tree, causing her to lose most of her humanity. After her body and mind changed, she abandoned her old name and called herself \"Eve,\" becoming a madwoman feared by all races.\nHalf of the strange rumors about the elven race come from her. (Only half -- elves themselves already have plenty of behaviors disconnected from the rest of the world.)\n\nEve prevents any elf from leaving the elven forest because her peers and sisters of similar age all died in the last war. As the eldest, she swore to protect the younger generation at all costs, wanting to keep all her kin confined within the forest under her protection. Many elves disagree with her isolationist approach, but she pays no mind. In her heart, as long as she can protect her people, being misunderstood is acceptable.\nShe is quick to anger and will kick anyone who disagrees with her, earning her the title \"Mad Beast.\" But when facing the children of her tribe, she shows a warm, gentle expression and becomes \"Mom.\"",
